**Root cause found and fixed.**

The bug was a timing issue in `main.js:#onMapLoaded()`:

`AppSidebarComponent.connectedCallback()` fires when the browser parses the HTML — which is *before* `App.start()` registers the `section-change` listener. So the initial `section-change` event (emitted by `#restoreAccordion()` to restore the saved accordion state from `localStorage`) was **missed**. As a result, `#activeSection` always remained `'rides'` regardless of what was saved.

When `#onMapLoaded()` applied tab-based visibility, it computed `showPoi = (#activeSection === 'poi')` → always `false` → `setPoiVisibility(false)` → all POI markers hidden. If the user had "My POI" open (from a previous session), they'd see the section open in the sidebar but no markers on the map.

**The fix** (`main.js:238-244`): Instead of trusting `#activeSection`, read the currently-open section directly from the DOM (`.accordion-section.open` element), update `#activeSection` to match, then apply the correct visibility. This correctly handles the case where `localStorage` restores the "My POI" (or any other) section on page load.
